=2015-04-24|via=[[Internet Archive]]}}\n* {{cite book|first=Carter Goodwin|last=Woodson|author-link=Carter G. Woodson|year=1919|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=U6sQAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA91#v=onepage&q&f=false|title=The Education of the Negro Prior to 1861|edition=Second|location=Washington, D.C.|publisher=The Associated Publishers, Inc.|lccn=68029024|oclc=1003200476|accessdate=April 15, 2020|via=[[Google Books]]}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category-inline|Benjamin Banneker}}\n\n{{Portal bar|Biography|History|United States|Maryland}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Banneker, Mythology and legacy of Benjamin}}\n[[Category:African-American culture]]\n[[Category:American folklore]]\n[[Category:Misconceptions]]\n[[Category:Urban legends]]\n[[Category:Legacies by person]]\n", "name_user": "Corker1", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBanneker's clock:editorial change", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mythology_of_Benjamin_Banneker"}
{"title_page": "List of podcatchers", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nA '''podcatcher''', or '''podcast client''', is a computer program used to download various media via an [[RSS]] or [[XML]] feed.<ref name=\"Herrington2005-07\">{{cite book|first=Jack D.|last=Herrington|title=Podcasting Hacks|url=https://archive.org/details/podcastinghackst0000herr|url-access=registration|year=2005|publisher=O'Reilly Media, Inc.|isbn=978-0-596-10066-7|page=[https://archive.org/details/podcastinghackst0000herr/page/7 7]}}</ref><ref name=\"Herrington2005-10\">{{cite book|first=Jack D.|last=Herrington|title=Podcasting Hacks|url=https://archive.org/details/podcastinghackst0000herr|url-access=registration|year=2005|publisher=O'Reilly Media, Inc.|isbn=978-0-596-10066-7|page=[https://archive.org/details/podcastinghackst0000herr/page/10 10]}}</ref><ref name=\"O'SullivanGoerzen2008\">{{cite book|first1=Bryan|last1=O'Sullivan|first2=John|last2=Goerzen|first3=Donald Bruce|last3=Stewart|title=Real World Haskell|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=nh0okI1a1sQC&pg=PA505|date=15 November 2008|publisher=O'Reilly Media, Inc.|isbn=978-0-596-55430-9|page=505|quote=The idea of a podcatcher is simple. It is given a list of URLs to process. Downloading each of these URLs results in an XML file in the RSS format. Inside this ...}}</ref>\n\nWhile podcatchers are best known for downloading [[podcast]]s (generally audio files in [[MP3]] format or similar), many are also capable of downloading video, [[newsfeed]]s, text, and pictures. Some of these podcatchers can also automate the transfer of received audio files to a [[portable media player]]. Although many include a directory of high-profile podcasts, they generally allow users to manually subscribe directly to a feed by providing the [[URL]].\n\nThe core concepts [[history of podcasting|had been developing since 2000]], the first commercial podcast client software was developed in 2001,<ref name=Voices2015>{{cite web|last1=Ciccarelli|first1=Stephanie|title=History of Podcasting|url=https://www.voices.com/resources/articles/podcasting/history-of-podcasting|website=Voices.com|publisher=Interactive Voices, Inc.|accessdate=3 April 2015}}</ref> and podcasting became popular in 2004.<ref name=\"Macnamara2010\">{{cite book|first=Jim|last=Macnamara|title=The 21st Century Media (r)evolution: Emergent Communication Practices|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rOal8bRULroC&pg=PA50|year=2010|publisher=Lang, Peter|isbn=978-1-4331-0936-2|page=50}}</ref>\n\nWhen [[Apple Inc.|Apple]] added podcatching to its [[iTunes]] software in June 2005, it almost immediately became the most popular client.<ref name=\"Braun2007\">{{cite book|first=Linda W.|last=Braun|title=Listen Up!: Podcasting for Schools and Libraries|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=b7QaEuV52VEC&pg=PA6|date=January 2007|publisher=Information Today, Inc.|isbn=978-1-57387-304-8|page=6}}</ref>\n\n== Podcatchers ==\nThe following is a list of noteworthy podcatchers or software with podcatching capability.<ref group=\"nb\"  name=\"noteworthy\">A podcatcher is presumed noteworthy if it has received significant coverage in [[Wikipedia:Reliable sources|reliable sources]] that are [[Wikipedia:Verifiability#Sources|independent]] of the company and satisfies the [[Wikipedia:Notability|inclusion criteria]] for a stand-alone article.</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\"\n\n|-\n! Title !!class=\"unsortable\"| Description !! License\n!class=\"unsortable\"|Latest release date!! Operating system\n|-\n| [[Amarok (software)|Amarok]] || Music player and podcast client || GPL v2\n|{{release date and age|2015|08|16}}\n| [[FreeBSD]], [[Linux]]\n|-\n|[[AntennaPod]] || Podcast manager for Android ||[[MIT License|MIT]]\n|{{release date and age|2019|05|27}}\n| Android\n|-\n| [[Banshee (media player)|Banshee]] || Music player and podcast client || MIT\n|{{release date and age|2014|03|18}}\n| [[Linux]], macOS, Windows\n|-\n| [[Clementine (software)|Clementine]] || A cross-platform fork of Amarok ||[[GPL]]\n|{{release date and age|2016|04|19}}\n| [[Linux]], Windows, macOS\n|-\n| [[doubleTwist]] ||  Android music player with podcast directory and podcast support. || \n|{{release date and age|2007|03}}\n| Android\n|-\n| [[Feedbooks]] ||  Social networking client with support for podcasts. || \n|{{release date and age|2014|04}}\n| Windows\n|-\n| [[Foobar2000]] ||  Versatile audio player with separate podcatcher component ||[[Donationware]]\n|{{release date and age|2017|04|07}}\n| Windows\n|-\n|[[Google Podcasts]]||  ||{{proprietary}}\n|\n|[[Android (operating system)|Android]]\n|-\n| {{ill|gPodder|fr}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://cybernetnews.com/gpodder-a-full-featured-podcast-client-for-linux/|title=gPodder \u2013 A Full Featured Podcast Client for Linux|last=cybernetnews.com|website=cybernetnews.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-11-16}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://twit.tv/shows/floss-weekly/episodes/272|title=FLOSS Weekly 272 gPodder - TWiT.TV|author=|date=|website=TWiT.tv|accessdate=9 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lifewire.com/subscribe-and-manage-podcasts-using-gpodder-4066928|title=Find And Listen To Your Favourite Podcasts Using Linux|author=|date=|website=lifewire.com|accessdate=9 April 2018}}</ref>|| simple, open source podcast client written in Python || GPL 3\n|{{release date and age|2018|2|19}}\n| [[Windows]], [[Linux]], [[macOS]] and others\n|-\n| [[iTunes]]|| Music and podcaster client || {{proprietary}} \n|{{release date and age|2019|03|25}}\n| [[Windows]], [[macOS]]\n|-\n|[[Juice (aggregator)|Juice]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.castpodder.net:80/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060302062022/http://www.castpodder.net:80/|url-status=dead|archive-date=2006-03-02|title=CastPodder - A Linux podcast agregrator|date=2006-03-02|access-date=2019-06-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://sourceforge.net/projects/icepodder/|title=IcePodder Podcatcher/RSS client|author=|date=|website=SourceForge|accessdate=9 April 2018}}</ref>|| A cross-platform podcatcher (discontinued) || GPL\n|{{release date and age|2006|07|18}}||[[Windows]], [[macOS]]\n|-\n| [[Liferea]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lzone.de/liferea/|title=Liferea - the Free News Aggregator on your Linux desktop|author=|date=|website=lzone.de|accessdate=9 April 2018}}</ref>|| News aggregator for online news feeds, features podcast support || GPL\n|{{release date and age|2016|12|27}}\n|[[Linux]]\n|-\n|[[Media Go]]|| Similar to [[iTunes]] for [[Sony]] [[PlayStation Portable]]|| {{proprietary}} \n| ||[[Windows]]\n|-\n| [[MediaMonkey]]|| Media organizers with integrated podcatcher || {{proprietary}} \n|{{release date and age|2017|02|26}}\n| [[Windows]]\n|-\n|[[Miro (software)|Miro]]|| An integrated video player with podcatcher capabilities (discontinued) || GPL v2\n|{{release date and age|2013|04|16}}\n|[[Windows]], [[Linux]], [[macOS]]\n|-\n| [[MusicBee]]|| Music player with integrated podcatcher || {{proprietary}} \n|{{release date and age|2017|03|10}}\n|[[Windows]]\n|-\n| [[NetNewsWire]]|| An RSS and Atom newsreader || {{proprietary}} \n| ||[[macOS]]\n|-\n|[[NewsFire]]|| A news reader and podcast client for MacOS X. There is no option for independent download || {{proprietary}} \n| ||[[macOS]]\n|-\n|[[Overcast (app)|Overcast]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Summers|first1=Nick|title=Meet Overcast, a new iPhone podcast app from Instapaper founder Marco Arment|url=https://thenextweb.com/apps/2014/07/16/overcast-review/|website=The Next Web|publisher=The Next Web|accessdate=24 February 2016}}</ref>|| A free podcast client for Apple Watch, iPad, and iPhone || {{proprietary}} \n|{{release date and age|2019|07|21}}\n| [[iOS]], [[watchOS]]\n|-\n|[[Pocket Casts]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Pierce|first1=David|title=Pocket Casts Is the Podcast App Every iPhone User Needs|url=https://www.wired.com/2016/07/pocket-casts-podcast-app-every-iphone-user-needs/|publisher=Wired|accessdate=27 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Welch|first1=Chris|title=One of the best podcast apps, Pocket Casts, just got a big redesign|url=https://www.theverge.com/2018/11/14/18094835/pocket-casts-7-app-features-redesign-podcasts-ios-android|publisher=The Verge|accessdate=27 May 2019}}</ref>|| A cross-platform podcast client || {{proprietary}} \n|{{release date and age|2019|05|16}}\n| [[iOS]], [[Android (operating system)|Android]], [[watchOS]], [[Windows]], [[macOS]] and [[Web application|Web]]\n|-\n| [[Podwalk]] || A podcast client for location-specific podcasts. || {{proprietary}} \n|{{release date and age|2017|02|01}}\n| [[iOS]]\n|-\n| [[Radio UserLand]] ||  A blogging tool and RSS newsreader || {{proprietary}} \n|{{release date and age|2005|09|06}}|| [[Windows]], [[classic Mac OS]], [[macOS]]\n|-\n| [[Rhythmbox]] || Default music management application for GNOME || GPL v2\n|{{release date and age|2016|09|10}}\n| [[Linux]]\n|-\n|[[Spotify]]<ref>{{Cite web|title = Say hello to the most entertaining Spotify ever|url = https://news.spotify.com/us/2015/05/20/say-hello-to-the-most-entertaining-spotify-ever/|accessdate = 2015-05-21|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150626214332/https://news.spotify.com/us/2015/05/20/say-hello-to-the-most-entertaining-spotify-ever/|archive-date = 2015-06-26|url-status = dead}}</ref>\n|(Podcasts not yet available for most formats) A commercial music streaming service with podcast support\n|{{proprietary}}\n|\n|[[Windows]], [[Linux]], [[Android (operating system)|Android]], [[iOS]], [[Chrome OS]], [[macOS]], [[Sony PlayStation]], and [[Web application|Web]]\n|-\n| [[Stitcher]] || Radio station and podcast client ||{{proprietary}} \n||| [[Android (operating system)|Android]], [[iOS]], [[Web application|Web]]\n|-\n| [[VLC media player|VLC]]<ref>{{Cite web|title=VLC subscribe to podcasts|url=http://en.kioskea.net/faq/9857-vlc-subscribe-to-podcasts|date=13 June 2015}}</ref>|| Cross-platform multimedia player and framework, includes a podcast subscription featu