007|publisher=Information Today, Inc.|isbn=978-1-57387-304-8|page=6}}</ref>\n\n== Podcatchers ==\nThe following is a list of noteworthy podcatchers or software with podcatching capability.<ref group=\"nb\"  name=\"noteworthy\">A podcatcher is presumed noteworthy if it has received significant coverage in [[Wikipedia:Reliable sources|reliable sources]] that are [[Wikipedia:Verifiability#Sources|independent]] of the company and satisfies the [[Wikipedia:Notability|inclusion criteria]] for a stand-alone article.</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\"\n\n|-\n! Title !!class=\"unsortable\"| Description !! License\n!class=\"unsortable\"|Latest release date!! Operating system\n|-\n| [[Amarok (software)|Amarok]] || Music player and podcast client || GPL v2\n|{{release date and age|2015|08|16}}\n| [[FreeBSD]], [[Linux]]\n|-\n|[[AntennaPod]] || Podcast manager for Android ||[[MIT License|MIT]]\n|{{release date and age|2019|05|27}}\n| Android\n|-\n| [[Banshee (media player)|Banshee]] || Music player and podcast client || MIT\n|{{release date and age|2014|03|18}}\n| [[Linux]], macOS, Windows\n|-\n| [[Clementine (software)|Clementine]] || A cross-platform fork of Amarok ||[[GPL]]\n|{{release date and age|2016|04|19}}\n| [[Linux]], Windows, macOS\n|-\n| [[doubleTwist]] ||  Android music player with podcast directory and podcast support. || \n|{{release date and age|2007|03}}\n| Android\n|-\n| [[Feedbooks]] ||  Social networking client with support for podcasts. || \n|{{release date and age|2014|04}}\n| Windows\n|-\n| [[Foobar2000]] ||  Versatile audio player with separate podcatcher component ||[[Donationware]]\n|{{release date and age|2017|04|07}}\n| Windows\n|-\n|[[Google Podcasts]]||  ||{{proprietary}}\n|\n|[[Android (operating system)|Android]]\n|-\n| {{ill|gPodder|fr}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://cybernetnews.com/gpodder-a-full-featured-podcast-client-for-linux/|title=gPodder \u2013 A Full Featured Podcast Client for Linux|last=cybernetnews.com|website=cybernetn